The paper focuses on using unlabeled video data to learn a model of scene dynamics for video recognition and generation tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions experiments and visualizations, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the impact of generative video models on video understanding and simulation, which suggests that it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
